# Page Object Model Standards

## Structure

- Every page class must extend `BasePage` from `./base.page.ts`.
- Define `readonly path: string` for the page URL path.
- Declare all locators as `readonly` class properties in the constructor.
- Use user-facing locators (`getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByLabel`).

## Methods

- Name action methods with verbs: `clickGetStarted()`, `searchRoute()`.
- Name assertion methods with `expect` prefix: `expectHeroVisible()`, `expectPageLoaded()`.
- Keep page objects free of test assertions that are test-specific — only include reusable assertions.

## Example Pattern

```typescript
export class MyPage extends BasePage {
  readonly path = '/my-page';
  readonly heading: Locator;

  constructor(page: Page) {
    super(page);
    this.heading = page.getByRole('heading', { name: /my page/i });
  }

  async expectPageLoaded() {
    await expect(this.heading).toBeVisible();
  }
}
```

## Registration

After creating a new page object:
1. Export it from `src/pages/index.ts`.
2. Add it as a fixture in `src/fixtures/test.fixture.ts`.
